Last Of The Summer Wine - Series 29 - Episode 10

It&#039;s Never Ten Years

BBC One - 24 August 2008

Clegg and Truly reminisce fondly about their old friend Compo, who suffered at the hands of Nora Batty - and them.

The longest running comedy series in the world started out, as many British comedy successes did, with a 1973 episode of the BBC series "Comedy Playhouse".
The basis was simple but complex at the same time. It tells us the stories of three old men, who in all essence couldn&#039;t be more young at heart.
